## Overview

Brad Sherman advocated against the separation of church and state, calling it a [“myth”](https://www.press-citizen.com/story/news/politics/elections/2022/10/26/iowa-house-district-91-election-2022-williamsburg-republican-brad-sherman-democrat-elle-wyant/69525913007/) and urging for greater Christian influence over the American government. Sherman was also a part of religious leaders who believed Trump’s presidential win was [“ordained by God.”](https://www.reuters.com/world/us/how-trump-netted-evangelical-votes-iowa-with-help-young-christian-operative-2023-12-14/) During a prayer at a Cedar Rapids Rally in 2023, Sherman said [“the gates of Hell will not prevail”](https://www.reuters.com/world/us/how-trump-netted-evangelical-votes-iowa-with-help-young-christian-operative-2023-12-14/) over Trump and said it was God’s “calling” for Trump to win the election.

## Brad Sherman Called The Separation Of Church And State A “Myth” And Advocated For Christianity In The American Government

### Sherman Called the Separation Of Church And State A “Myth” And Urged For Greater Christian Influence Over Government 

**2022: Sherman Advocated Against The Separation Of Church And State.** According to the Iowa City Press-Citizen, “Sherman is campaigning on political views like denying the 2020 presidential election results and advocating against the separation of church and state.” \[Iowa City Press-Citizen, [10/26/22](https://www.press-citizen.com/story/news/politics/elections/2022/10/26/iowa-house-district-91-election-2022-williamsburg-republican-brad-sherman-democrat-elle-wyant/69525913007/)\]

**2022: Sherman Called Separation Of Church And State A “Myth” And Urged For A “Stronger Presence” Of Christianity In Government.** According to the Iowa City Press-Citizen, “Sherman uses the sites to express the belief that church and state should not be separated and called the separation inclusion in the First Amendment ‘a myth.’ While he said he doesn't want to force Christianity on others, he advocates for a stronger presence of the religion in government.” \[Iowa City Press-Citizen, [10/26/22](https://www.press-citizen.com/story/news/politics/elections/2022/10/26/iowa-house-district-91-election-2022-williamsburg-republican-brad-sherman-democrat-elle-wyant/69525913007/)\]
